  "prompt": "How do I easily transfer contacts, messages and photos from one Android phone to another?",
  "response": "Here are several methods to transfer data between Android phones:\n\n1. Google Account Sync\n- Automatically backs up contacts, calendar, and app data\n- Go to Settings > Accounts > Google > Sync\n- Enable sync for contacts and other data\n- Sign in with same Google account on new phone\n\n2. Google Drive Backup\n- Back up photos, videos, and app data\n- Settings > System > Backup\n- Enable Google Drive backup\n- Restore on new phone during setup\n\n3. Samsung Smart Switch\n- For Samsung phones\n- Download app on both old and new phones\n- Transfer wirelessly or via USB cable\n\n4. Google Photos\n- Automatically backs up photos and videos\n- Install app, enable backup in settings\n- Sign in with same account on new phone\n\n5. Third-party Apps\n- Apps like Move to Android (by Google)\n- Send Anywhere\n- SHAREit\n- Help transfer multiple types of data\n\n6. Direct Cable Transfer\n- Use USB-C or USB OTG cable\n- Connect phones directly\n- Manually copy files\n\n7. Bluetooth\n- Slower method\n- Good for smaller file transfers\n- Pair phones and send files\n\nRecommended: Use Google services for easiest, most comprehensive transfer.",
